                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1400" notAfter="1499">15th century</date>
                        <desc>
                           Archaic and recent paleographic features coexist: 
                           ሎ has sometimes the loop marking the 7th order attached directly to the body of the letter, sometimes by means of the linking line; 
                           some letters, e.g. ቆ, ቶ, የ, ደ, ጸ, and ዐ have an angular shape; 
                           ፪ has angular and not separated loops.
                        </desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication"/>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The shelfmark <q xml:lang="la">Vat. | 23 | aethiop.</q> is written on the cover, together with the coat of arms of pope <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6258LeoXIII">Leo XIII</persName> 
                              and of the librarian <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11256PitraGB">Giovanni Battista Pitra</persName>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <locus target="#1r" facs="0002"/>
                           <desc>The shelfmark <q xml:lang="la">Aeth. 23</q> and <q xml:lang="la">Aethiop. 23</q> are written in pale black ink at the bottom of the leaf and on the sheet glued to the top the leaf.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>
                              Number of the sections are written in small script in black or red ink, in the margin. Liturgical directives are inserted either within the text or in the upper margin. 
                              They are accompanied by the words <q xml:lang="gez">ዝየ፡</q> or <q xml:lang="gez">ቍም፡</q>, written in abbreviated form and indicating the beginning of the sections. 
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                       </list>
                  </additions>
            
